cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of 3D human modeling using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and focuses on extracting features from two orthogonal silhouettes of individuals. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves generating 3D models, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of supervised learning and CNNs suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new CNN structure for 3D human modeling, which indicates that it may also belong to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
